The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques for predicting emojis in tweets. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also uses a Multi-channel Convolutional Neural Network, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses subword embeddings, which is a technique used in both cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval (IR) to some extent, as it involves predicting emojis based on the text in tweets.
